Week 1
Friday — Lab Environment Creation
Objective

Build the base virtual lab environment that will host the Active Directory infrastructure.

Architecture

Two virtual machines were created:

• Domain Controller (Windows Server)
• Client Workstation (Windows 10)

Both machines were configured to operate on a private internal virtual network to simulate a corporate LAN.

Setup Steps

Installed VirtualBox hypervisor.

Created Windows Server VM for the Domain Controller.

Created Windows 10 VM for the client workstation.

Configured networking:

Internal network adapter for lab communication

NAT adapter temporarily used for internet access.

Assigned a static IP address to the Domain Controller.

Example configuration:

DC IP

192.168.10.10
Result

A basic isolated lab network capable of supporting domain services.

Saturday — Active Directory Domain Installation
Objective

Promote the Windows Server machine to a Domain Controller.

Architecture

The Domain Controller hosts:

• Active Directory Domain Services
• DNS Server

Domain name created:

company.local
Build Steps

Installed Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS) role.

Promoted the server to a Domain Controller.

Created a new forest.

Installed and configured DNS automatically during promotion.

Rebooted server to finalize domain creation.

Result

A fully functioning Active Directory forest and domain was created.

