Week 2
Wednesday — DNS and Network Troubleshooting
Objective

Diagnose and resolve network connectivity issues affecting domain communication.

Issues Encountered

Client machine received AutoConfiguration address:

169.254.x.x

This prevented proper DNS communication.

Troubleshooting Steps

Verified DNS service status on DC.

Confirmed correct DNS server address on client.

Reset network adapter configuration.

Verified network adapter settings in VirtualBox.

Reconfigured adapters for correct routing.

Result

Client was able to resolve:

company.local

and communicate with the Domain Controller.

Thursday — Group Policy Management
Objective

Implement Group Policy to control workstation behavior.

Architecture
Domain Controller
   ↓
Group Policy Objects
   ↓
Domain Clients
Build Steps

Installed Group Policy Management tools (RSAT).

Opened Group Policy Management Console.

Created new GPO.

Example policy implemented:

Disable Control Panel access

Linked GPO to the Users OU.

Forced policy update:

gpupdate /force
Result

Client workstation successfully applied the new domain policy.

